A secure file encryption tool built in Python that uses AES-256-GCM — the same standard used in real-world security applications. Whether you're protecting sensitive documents or just learning how encryption works under the hood, this tool has you covered.
What makes it solid:

Encrypt files using a password or a key file — your choice
Tamper detection built in — if anyone modifies your encrypted file, decryption will fail and tell you
Keys are generated using cryptographically secure randomness, not random()
Deleted files are overwritten with random data (3 passes) before removal — not just sent to Trash
Works three ways: CLI, interactive menu, or import it directly as a Python class

Built with:
Python · AES-256-GCM · PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256 · cryptography library
Known limitations:

Loads the entire file into memory — very large files may cause slowdowns
Secure delete currently overwrites only the first 1MB per pass



Built as part of a personal cybersecurity learning journey. Follows cryptography best practices throughout.
